# === WALLET / KEY / SEED PROTECTION ===
# Added 2026-04-11 ahead of Iskander wallet installation (per the cooperative's
# financial-sovereignty driver). These patterns NEVER reach version control.
# If you find a file matching any of these patterns in the worktree, halt and
# ask Lola before any commit. Invariant #2 (agents draft, humans sign): Et never
# holds signing keys; only the propose-key pattern from tx_orchestrator.py.
# Red-team standing paramount objection enforces this absolutely.

# Generic wallet directories
wallets/
wallet/
*-wallet/
.wallet/
keys/
keystore/
keystores/
.keystore
.keystores

# Common wallet file patterns
*.key
*.keystore
*.keystore.json
*.seed
*.mnemonic
*.wallet
*.wallet.json
mnemonic.txt
mnemonic.md
seed.txt
seed.md
recovery.txt
recovery-phrase.*
private-key.*
private_key.*

# Specific wallet tooling outputs
geth-keystore/
parity-keystore/
besu-keystore/
hardhat-keystore/
foundry-keystore/
ledger-export.*
trezor-export.*

# Gnosis Safe / multisig drafts that might leak human signers
.gnosis-safe-cache/
safe-tx-drafts/

# Iskander-specific (treasury operational data)
iskander-treasury/
iskander-wallets/
treasury-cache/
treasury-state/

# Hardware wallet integration files (defensive)
*.hwi
*.hwi.json

# Environment variable files for chain RPC + wallet config
.env.wallet
.env.treasury
.env.chain
secrets/wallet/
secrets/keys/

# Generated address books (these CAN be public, but may contain pre-publication
# state — Steward agent decides when to promote them to the public reporting layer)
address-book.json
.address-cache/

# === END WALLET / KEY / SEED PROTECTION ===
